						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Pallava, Narendrap-pottaraiyan = c. 800 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Tamil verse recording the excavation of the cave called Śatrumallēśvarālayam dedicated to Śiva by the king who was wearing the garland of Toṇḍai flowers. (This seems to be a later Tamil rendering of the following Sanskrit inscription of Mahēndravarman I). Composed by Brahmamaṅgalavaṉ Chellan Śivadāsan a local resident.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">EpigraphiaIndica</hi>, vol. XII, pp. 225-26.)</p>						

						</summary>
